// ==WindhawkMod==
// @id              taskbar-media-controller
// @name            Taskbar Media Controller
// @description     Taskbar widget with media controls and now playing info.
// @version         1.2.0
// @author          vyr0
// @github          https://github.com/vyr0-the-dev
// @include         explorer.exe
// @compilerOptions -lole32 -ldwmapi -lgdi32 -luser32 -lwindowsapp -lshcore -lgdiplus -lshell32 -lmmdevapi
// ==/WindhawkMod==

// ==WindhawkModReadme==
/*
A sleek taskbar widget that shows your currently playing music with playback controls and volume slider.

## Features

- **Now Playing** — Displays song title, artist, and album art from any app using Windows media transport controls (Spotify, YouTube Music, Tidal, etc.)
- **Playback Controls** — Previous, play/pause, and next buttons with hover animations
- **Volume Slider** — Appears on hover to control system volume directly from the taskbar
- **Progress Bar** — Thin progress bar at the bottom showing playback position with smooth interpolation
- **Album Art Glow** — Subtle glow effect behind album art using its dominant color
- **Album Art Tooltip** — Hover over album art to see full song info (title, artist, duration)
- **Song Transition Animation** — Smooth fade animation when the song changes
- **Multi-Monitor Support** — Shows on the taskbar of the active monitor (when multiple taskbars exist)
- **Album Art** — Shows album artwork with rounded corners, or a music note placeholder when unavailable
- **Auto Theme** — Automatically switches text color between light and dark based on your Windows theme
- **Album Color Mode** — Extracts the dominant color from album art for text/icons
- **Acrylic Background** — Optional frosted glass effect with adjustable opacity
- **Scrolling Text** — Long song titles scroll automatically when they don't fit
- **Hide in Fullscreen** — Optionally hides the panel when a fullscreen app is active
- **Idle Timeout** — Auto-hide after a configurable period of no playback
- **Customizable** — Adjust size, position, font size, button scale, and colors

## Usage

1. Enable the mod and the widget will appear on your taskbar
2. Hover over the panel to reveal playback controls and volume slider
3. Click the buttons to control media playback
4. Click on the progress bar to seek to a different position
5. Hover over album art to see full song information
6. Adjust settings in the Windhawk UI to customize appearance and behavior

## Requirements

- Windows 10/11 with taskbar
- A media app that supports Windows media transport controls (most modern music/video players)

## Configuration

All settings are available in the Windhawk mod settings panel:
- **Panel size** — Width and height in pixels
- **Position** — X/Y offset from the taskbar edge
- **Theme** — Auto, manual hex color, or album art color
- **Background** — Acrylic blur opacity (0-255)
- **Buttons** — Scale factor (0.5x to 4.0x)
- **Progress Bar** — Show/hide the progress bar at the bottom
- **Album Glow** — Enable/disable the glow effect behind album art
- **Tooltip** — Show/hide song info on album art hover
- **Transition Animation** — Enable/disable fade effect on song changes
- **Multi-Monitor** — Show on active monitor's taskbar (multi-monitor setups)
- **Behavior** — Hide in fullscreen, idle timeout, volume slider toggle
*/
// ==/WindhawkModReadme==

// ==WindhawkModSettings==
/*
- PanelWidth: 300
  $name: Panel width
  $description: Width of the music panel in pixels.
- PanelHeight: 48
  $name: Panel height
  $description: Height of the music panel in pixels.
- FontSize: 11
  $name: Font size
  $description: Font size for song title and artist.
- OffsetX: 12
  $name: Offset X
  $description: Horizontal offset from the left edge of the taskbar.
- OffsetY: 0
  $name: Offset Y
  $description: Vertical offset from the center of the taskbar.
- AutoTheme: true
  $name: Auto theme
  $description: Automatically adjust text color based on system light/dark theme.
- AlbumColor: false
  $name: Album art color
  $description: Use the dominant color from the album art for text and icons. Overrides AutoTheme and manual text color when enabled.
- TextColor: FFFFFF
  $name: Manual text color
  $description: Text color in hex (e.g. FFFFFF for white). Only used when AutoTheme is off and AlbumColor is off.
- ButtonScale: "1.0"
  $name: Button scale
  $description: Scale factor for playback control buttons (0.5 to 4.0).
- BgOpacity: 0
  $name: Background opacity
  $description: Acrylic background opacity from 0 (transparent) to 255 (opaque).
- HideFullscreen: false
  $name: Hide in fullscreen
  $description: Hide the panel when a fullscreen application is active.
- IdleTimeout: 0
  $name: Idle timeout
  $description: Hide the panel after this many seconds of no music playing. 0 to disable.
- ShowVolume: true
  $name: Show volume slider
  $description: Display a volume slider next to playback controls when hovered.
- ShowProgress: true
  $name: Show progress bar
  $description: Display a thin progress bar at the bottom showing playback position.
- AlbumGlow: true
  $name: Album art glow
  $description: Show a subtle glow behind album art using its dominant color.
- ShowTooltip: true
  $name: Album art tooltip
  $description: Show full song info popup when hovering over album art.
- TransitionAnim: true
  $name: Song transition animation
  $description: Smooth fade animation when song changes.
- MultiMonitor: true
  $name: Multi-monitor taskbar
  $description: Show on the taskbar of the monitor where media is playing (if multiple taskbars exist).
*/
// ==/WindhawkModSettings==

